<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>Necromancer</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/SSETHLORTH.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  SSETHLORTH<br>Level 65 Necromancer<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><br>Raid Commander<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=SSETHLORTH"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">SSETHLORTH</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=25&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>Ah...so I guess it is my time to speak for the dead summoners. I promise no books though...since levelin' our class solo should have taught you all the lessons you need to know.<br><br>The Raid:<br><br>Lesson 1- "Know Thy Self"<br>The necro class is an utility class that has many stand-alone resources to draw upon in the time of battle. We are one of the least understood classes in group situations, since few see our potential in direct aid to a group. We are DPS over time. In long engages, we can out damage a wizard easly..and still almost be full mana. We can round a group out by adding redundancy: tank with pet, heal self and others, sieve/give mana, snare, mez, slow dead, feign pull, or rez. Our ablilities can give us much pride in our work. But, we must keep our pride in check...we can act like others classes at times, but never be as good at what they do at that task.<br><br>Lesson 2- "Know Thy Friends"<br>Remember you are grouped. You might be able to feign off danger, but the others you are with probably can't. In raiding situations, part of your mana pool belongs to the raid AT ALL TIMES. You can speed up buffin' sessions after MGB's and keep your group healer in 'happy times' during engagements. Group heal/mana dots help against AoE mobs and should be used whenever possible with your damage dots. Keeping your friends alive will keep you alive without having to feign and burn a few EE's or coffins.<br><br>Lesson 3- "Know Thy Enemy"<br>Necros have a good assortment of DPS to choose from in an encounter. Only useful line we don't have is a cold based dot, but that can always be worked around. <br>Fast fights require fast acting dots...balance your mana cost vs. damage vs. aggro. To this day at lv65, I still use "Splurt" for those reasons at times. Manage your aggro...FD usually can give a mem-wipe...so use it after casting a high aggro dot or series of dots. Ticking a mob for 400-800pts will get you summoned, if you don't keep things in check. Learn your high aggro spells. Chain casting snare on a mob will make any MA envious of your taunting ability. (Not a good thing =P) Pets can be useful in raid situations, only IF the mob doesn't have an AoE proc. Most endgame mobs require correct positioning from the MA and melee force...which can't be done if you are tryin' to spam you pet into not attacking. My only advice would be to train in AA's until your first big spend is in Pet Discipline skill. Only this will keep your pet in check, and allow you to have one in such an encounter.<br><br>So, those are just a few thoughts...Anyone is always welcome to tell me in game on solo tactics such as aggro kiting or research advice. Be safe in your travels.<br><br>Sseth<br clear=all></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
